{"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/gettingstarted"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to integrate the Composable Architecture into your project and write your first","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"application.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials","title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DependencyManagement","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingTCA","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Navigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Performance","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/FAQ"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Adding the Composable Architecture as a dependency","type":"heading","anchor":"Adding-the-Composable-Architecture-as-a-dependency","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To use the Composable Architecture in a SwiftPM project, add it to the dependencies of your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Package.swift and specify the "},{"code":"ComposableArchitecture","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" product in any targets that need access to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the library:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let package = Package(","  dependencies: [","    .package(","      url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-composable-architecture\",","      from: \"1.0.0\"","    ),","  ],","  targets: [","    .target(","      name: \"<target-name>\",","      dependencies: [","        .product(","          name: \"ComposableArchitecture\",","          package: \"swift-composable-architecture\"","        )","      ]","    )","  ]",")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Writing your first feature","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Writing-your-first-feature"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a step-by-step interactive tutorial, be sure to check out"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/MeetComposableArchitecture","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To build a feature using the Composable Architecture you define some types and values that model"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"your domain:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"State"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A type that describes the data your feature needs to perform its logic and render its"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"UI."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]},{"text":": A type that represents all of the actions that can happen in your feature, such as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"user actions, notifications, event sources and more."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reducer"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A function that describes how to evolve the current state of the app to the next"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"state given an action. The reducer is also responsible for returning any effects that should be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"run, such as API requests, which can be done by returning an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Effect"},{"type":"text","text":" value."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Store"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": The runtime that actually drives your feature. You send all user actions to the store"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"so that the store can run the reducer and effects, and you can observe state changes in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"store so that you can update UI.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The benefits of doing this are that you will instantly unlock testability of your feature, and you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be able to break large, complex features into smaller domains that can be glued together.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As a basic example, consider a UI that shows a number along with “+” and “−” buttons that increment","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and decrement the number. To make things interesting, suppose there is also a button that when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tapped makes an API request to fetch a random fact about that number and displays it in the view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To implement this feature we create a new type that will house the domain and behavior of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"feature, and it will be annotated with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer()","overridingTitle":"@Reducer","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Reducer"}],"isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" macro:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import ComposableArchitecture","","@Reducer","struct Feature {","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In here we need to define a type for the feature’s state, which consists of an integer for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current count, as well as an optional string that represents the fact being presented:"}]},{"code":["@Reducer","struct Feature {","  @ObservableState","  struct State: Equatable {","    var count = 0","    var numberFact: String?","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We’ve applied the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@ObservableState"},{"type":"text","text":" macro to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"State"},{"text":" in order to take advantage of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"observation tools in the library."}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We also need to define a type for the feature’s actions. There are the obvious actions, such as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tapping the decrement button, increment button, or fact button. But there are also some slightly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-obvious ones, such as the action that occurs when we receive a response from the fact API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"request:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Feature {","  @ObservableState","  struct State: Equatable { \/* ... *\/ }","  enum Action {","    case decrementButtonTapped","    case incrementButtonTapped","    case numberFactButtonTapped","    case numberFactResponse(String)","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And then we implement the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"type":"text","text":" property, which is responsible for composing the actual logic and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior for the feature. In it we can use the "},{"code":"Reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reducer to describe how to change the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current state to the next state, and what effects need to be executed. Some actions don’t need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"execute effects, and they can return "},{"code":".none","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to represent that:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Feature {","  @ObservableState","  struct State: Equatable { \/* ... *\/ }","  enum Action { \/* ... *\/ }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      switch action {","      case .decrementButtonTapped:","        state.count -= 1","        return .none","","      case .incrementButtonTapped:","        state.count += 1","        return .none","","      case .numberFactButtonTapped:","        return .run { [count = state.count] send in","          let (data, _) = try await URLSession.shared.data(","            from: URL(string: \"http:\/\/numbersapi.com\/\\(count)\/trivia\")!","          )","          await send(","            .numberFactResponse(String(decoding: data, as: UTF8.self))","          )","        }","","      case let .numberFactResponse(fact):","        state.numberFact = fact","        return .none","      }","    }","  }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"And then finally we define the view that displays the feature. It holds onto a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StoreOf<Feature>"},{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so that it can observe all changes to the state and re-render, and we can send all user actions to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the store so that state changes:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct FeatureView: View {","  let store: StoreOf<Feature>","","  var body: some View {","    Form {","      Section {","        Text(\"\\(store.count)\")","        Button(\"Decrement\") { store.send(.decrementButtonTapped) }","        Button(\"Increment\") { store.send(.incrementButtonTapped) }","      }","","      Section {","        Button(\"Number fact\") { store.send(.numberFactButtonTapped) }","      }","      ","      if let fact = store.numberFact {","        Text(fact)","      }","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is also straightforward to have a UIKit controller driven off of this store. You can observe","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"state changes in the store in ","type":"text"},{"code":"viewDidLoad","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and then populate the UI components with data from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the store. The code is a bit longer than the SwiftUI version, so we have collapsed it here:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["class FeatureViewController: UIViewController {","  let store: StoreOf<Feature>","","  init(store: StoreOf<Feature>) {","    self.store = store","    super.init(nibName: nil, bundle: nil)","  }","","  required init?(coder: NSCoder) {","    fatalError(\"init(coder:) has not been implemented\")","  }","","  override func viewDidLoad() {","    super.viewDidLoad()","","    let countLabel = UILabel()","    let decrementButton = UIButton()","    let incrementButton = UIButton()","    let factLabel = UILabel()","    ","    \/\/ Omitted: Add subviews and set up constraints...","    ","    observe { [weak self] in","      guard let self ","      else { return }","      ","      countLabel.text = \"\\(self.store.text)\"","      factLabel.text = self.store.numberFact","    }","  }","","  @objc private func incrementButtonTapped() {","    self.store.send(.incrementButtonTapped)","  }","  @objc private func decrementButtonTapped() {","    self.store.send(.decrementButtonTapped)","  }","  @objc private func factButtonTapped() {","    self.store.send(.numberFactButtonTapped)","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once we are ready to display this view, for example in the app’s entry point, we can construct a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"store. This can be done by specifying the initial state to start the application in, as well as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the reducer that will power the application:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import ComposableArchitecture","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","  var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","      FeatureView(","        store: Store(initialState: Feature.State()) {","          Feature()","        }","      )","    }","  }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And that is enough to get something on the screen to play around with. It’s definitely a few more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"steps than if you were to do this in a vanilla SwiftUI way, but there are a few benefits. It gives"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"us a consistent manner to apply state mutations, instead of scattering logic in some observable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"objects and in various action closures of UI components. It also gives us a concise way of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"expressing side effects. And we can immediately test this logic, including the effects, without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doing much additional work."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Testing your feature","anchor":"Testing-your-feature","type":"heading","level":2},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more in-depth information on testing, see the dedicated "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingTCA","type":"reference"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"article."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To test use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore"},{"text":", which can be created with the same information as the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Store"},{"type":"text","text":", but it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"does extra work to allow you to assert how your feature evolves as actions are sent:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Test","func basics() async {","  let store = TestStore(initialState: Feature.State()) {","    Feature()","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once the test store is created we can use it to make an assertion of an entire user flow of steps."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Each step of the way we need to prove that state changed how we expect. For example, we can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simulate the user flow of tapping on the increment and decrement buttons:"}]},{"code":["\/\/ Test that tapping on the increment\/decrement buttons changes the count","await store.send(.incrementButtonTapped) {","  $0.count = 1","}","await store.send(.decrementButtonTapped) {","  $0.count = 0","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, if a step causes an effect to be executed, which feeds data back into the store, we must","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"assert on that. For example, if we simulate the user tapping on the fact button we expect to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"receive a fact response back with the fact, which then causes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numberFact"},{"type":"text","text":" state to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"populated:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["await store.send(.numberFactButtonTapped)","","await store.receive(\\.numberFactResponse) {","  $0.numberFact = ???","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"However, how do we know what fact is going to be sent back to us?","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Currently our reducer is using an effect that reaches out into the real world to hit an API server,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and that means we have no way to control its behavior. We are at the whims of our internet","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"connectivity and the availability of the API server in order to write this test.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It would be better for this dependency to be passed to the reducer so that we can use a live"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dependency when running the application on a device, but use a mocked dependency for tests. We can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"do this by adding a property to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Feature","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reducer:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Feature {","  let numberFact: (Int) async throws -> String","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then we can use it in the "},{"code":"reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" implementation:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["case .numberFactButtonTapped:","  return .run { [count = state.count] send in ","    let fact = try await self.numberFact(count)","    await send(.numberFactResponse(fact))","  }"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And in the entry point of the application we can provide a version of the dependency that actually"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"interacts with the real world API server:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@main","struct MyApp: App {","  var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","      FeatureView(","        store: Store(initialState: Feature.State()) {","          Feature(","            numberFact: { number in","              let (data, _) = try await URLSession.shared.data(","                from: URL(string: \"http:\/\/numbersapi.com\/\\(number)\")!","              )","              return String(decoding: data, as: UTF8.self)","            }","          )","        }","      )","    }","  }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"But in tests we can use a mock dependency that immediately returns a deterministic, predictable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fact:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Test","func basics() async {","  let store = TestStore(initialState: Feature.State()) {","    Feature(numberFact: { \"\\($0) is a good number Brent\" })","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With that little bit of upfront work we can finish the test by simulating the user tapping on the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fact button, and then receiving the response from the dependency to present the fact:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["await store.send(.numberFactButtonTapped)","","await store.receive(\\.numberFactResponse) {","  $0.numberFact = \"0 is a good number Brent\"","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We can also improve the ergonomics of using the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numberFact"},{"text":" dependency in our application. Over","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"time the application may evolve into many features, and some of those features may also want access","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numberFact"},{"type":"text","text":", and explicitly passing it through all layers can get annoying. There is a process"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can follow to “register” dependencies with the library, making them instantly available to any"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"layer in the application.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For more in-depth information on dependency management, see the dedicated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DependencyManagement","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" article.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We can start by wrapping the number fact functionality in a new type:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct NumberFactClient {","  var fetch: (Int) async throws -> String","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And then registering that type with the dependency management system by conforming the client to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DependencyKey"},{"text":" protocol, which requires you to specify the live value to use when running the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"application in simulators or devices:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension NumberFactClient: DependencyKey {","  static let liveValue = Self(","    fetch: { number in","      let (data, _) = try await URLSession.shared","        .data(from: URL(string: \"http:\/\/numbersapi.com\/\\(number)\")!","      )","      return String(decoding: data, as: UTF8.self)","    }","  )","}","","extension DependencyValues {","  var numberFact: NumberFactClient {","    get { self[NumberFactClient.self] }","    set { self[NumberFactClient.self] = newValue }","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With that little bit of upfront work done you can instantly start making use of the dependency in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any feature by using the "},{"code":"@Dependency","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property wrapper:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":[" @Reducer"," struct Feature {","-  let numberFact: (Int) async throws -> String","+  @Dependency(\\.numberFact) var numberFact","   ","   …","","-  try await self.numberFact(count)","+  try await self.numberFact.fetch(count)"," }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This code works exactly as it did before, but you no longer have to explicitly pass the dependency"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when constructing the feature’s reducer. When running the app in previews, the simulator or on a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"device, the live dependency will be provided to the reducer, and in tests the test dependency will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be provided.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This means the entry point to the application no longer needs to construct dependencies:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@main","struct MyApp: App {","  var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","      FeatureView(","        store: Store(initialState: Feature.State()) {","          Feature()","        }","      )","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And the test store can be constructed without specifying any dependencies, but you can still","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"override any dependency you need to for the purpose of the test:"}]},{"code":["let store = TestStore(initialState: Feature.State()) {","  Feature()","} withDependencies: {","  $0.numberFact.fetch = { \"\\($0) is a good number Brent\" }","}","","\/\/ ..."],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the basics of building and testing a feature in the Composable Architecture. There are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"a lot"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" more things to be explored. Be sure to check out the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/MeetComposableArchitecture"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tutorial, as well as dedicated articles on "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DependencyManagement","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingTCA"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Navigation"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Performance","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", and more. Also, the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-composable-architecture\/tree\/main\/Examples","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" directory has"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a bunch of projects to explore to see more advanced usages.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"Getting started","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/DependencyManagement":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to register dependencies with the library so that 